In his weekly address, President Trump discusses the approaching Hurricane Irma and the government's efforts to assist those affected. He emphasizes the importance of following recommendations from officials for safety. The President also highlights his recent visit to North Dakota, where he promoted tax cuts and tax reform as part of his economic policy. He states that the current tax code is burdensome and inhibits economic growth. The President's plan includes simplifying the tax filing process, cutting taxes for middle-class families, reducing the business tax rate, and making it easier for companies to repatriate money held overseas. He believes these measures will create jobs, raise wages, and make America economically dominant. The President concludes by expressing his commitment to making America great again.